          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                                        <date>June 27/51</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Dr Sir Your favor<lb/> of <date>10th</date> inst
                                        has been some time received.<lb/> I have been obliged to
                                        leave town for<lb/> some days since it reached me, or I
                                        would<lb/> have received my earlier attention. I<lb/> have
                                        collected $9 from <persName>A Moise Inn</persName>
                                        &amp;<lb/> will send to <persName>Mrs Griswold</persName>
                                        for the amt<lb/> due from her. <persName>Mr Joshua
                                                  Lazarus</persName> as<lb/> you are doubtless aware
                                        has left for<lb/>
                                        <placeName>Europe</placeName>. I ascertain thus far that<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mrs M L Cohen</persName><lb/>     <persName>John
                                                  I. Cohen</persName><lb/>     <persName>Leopold
                                                  Cohn</persName><lb/>
                                        <persName>Col M Jacobs</persName><lb/> are <hi
                                                  rend="underline">not</hi> subscribers to the
                                        Occident. My<lb/> friend <persName>P Wineman</persName> did
                                        not desire it<lb/> either, but (to please me I think)
                                        has<lb/> concluded to take it for the year at<lb/> any rate.
                                                  <persName>Mr B D
                                        Lazarus</persName><lb/>               &amp; <persName>B
                                                  Mordecai</persName><lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">marked with a star</hi> in yr list, I
                                        have<lb/> not yet seen. I have not had time<lb/> to solicit
                                        new subscribers, but yr list<lb/> is so full already in
                                                  <placeName>Charleston</placeName>, that<lb/> I
                                        know of few others to whom<lb/> application could be made.
                                        In the</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>cases of the 4 persons before named who<lb/> decline the Occident,
                                        I have not been<lb/> able to get numbers back. Some say<lb/>
                                        they did not get but <hi rend="underline">one</hi>
                                        number,<lb/> &amp; others that what they did get were<lb/>
                                                  ret<hi rend="underline">d</hi> &amp;c &amp;c I
                                        will endeavor to <hi rend="underline">retain</hi><lb/>
                                        <persName>B Mordecai</persName> &amp; <persName>B D
                                                  Lazarus</persName> if possible<lb/> I learn from
                                                  <persName>David Lopez</persName>, <persName>M H
                                                  Nathan</persName><lb/>
                                        <persName>M D Hyams</persName> &amp; <persName>N A
                                                  Cohen</persName> that their<lb/> withdrawal from
                                        yr subscription roll<lb/> originated from no objection to yr
                                        course<lb/> The two first did not want it &amp; had<lb/> no
                                        time to read it &amp; the two last had<lb/> copies in their
                                        houses taken by their<lb/> sons. I will inquire of
                                                  <persName>Jackson Moses</persName><lb/> whether he
                                        considers himself a subscriber<lb/> or, also of <persName>I.
                                                  L. DeLange</persName> &amp; <persName>J.
                                                  Harris</persName></p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">If anything can be done for the<lb/> Prayers &amp;
                                        Bible or Occident, I will<lb/> endeavor to accomplish it
                                        during<lb/> the ensuing dull season.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Yr Occident for <date>July</date> is at hand<lb/>
                                        It bears down manfully upon the<lb/> disorganizing clique
                                        who now rule<lb/> our congregational matters without<lb/>
                                        religion, without order &amp; without<lb/> law.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">It must do the Occident good with</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>Israelites <hi rend="underline">generally</hi>, 'altho with some
                                        of<lb/> the straggling followers of the now<lb/> dethroned
                                                  <persName>Posnanski</persName>
                                        dissatisfaction<lb/> may be created</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Of course this (the <hi rend="underline"
                                        >good</hi>,) is not the object, but<lb/> I for one will not
                                        object if it prove an<lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">incident</hi> to the publications
                                        referred<lb/> to.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I have to return you the regards<lb/> &amp; good
                                        wishes of the individuals,<lb/> to whom you desired
                                        remembrance<lb/> &amp; subscribe myself</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Yrs Truly &amp;c</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <persName role="author">Thos J Moise</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
